# ── Supabase (optional — enables cloud profiles) ──
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com/dashboard → New project
# 2. Project Settings → API: copy Project URL and anon public key
# 3. SQL Editor → run the SQL in supabase/schema.sql
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# ── Email Verification ──
# Choose ONE of the options below. Without either, users see "use 123456 to test".

# OPTION A — EmailJS (recommended, easiest — 5 min setup, no backend)
#
# 1. Create a free account at https://www.emailjs.com
# 2. EmailJS Dashboard → Email Services → Add Service (Gmail, Outlook, etc.)
#    Copy the Service ID (e.g. "service_abc123")
# 3. EmailJS Dashboard → Email Templates → Create New Template
#    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
#    │  To Email (REQUIRED!):  {{to_email}}                │
#    │  Subject:               Your {{app_name}} code      │
#    │  Body:                  Your code is: {{code}}      │
#    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
#    IMPORTANT: {{to_email}} goes in the "To Email" field at the TOP
#    of the template editor, NOT in the body. Without this you get
#    "The recipients address is empty".
#    Copy the Template ID (e.g. "template_xyz789")
# 4. EmailJS Dashboard → Account → General → copy your Public Key
# 5. Fill in the three values below and restart the dev server.
VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=
VITE_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=
VITE_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=

# OPTION B — Resend + Supabase Edge Functions (advanced, production-ready)
#
# 1. Get an API key from https://resend.com/api-keys (free: 100 emails/day)
# 2. In Supabase Dashboard → Edge Functions → set secret: RESEND_API_KEY = your key
# 3. Deploy: supabase functions deploy send-verification-code verify-code --no-verify-jwt
